  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally refers to the process of making illegally obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legal definitions typically include:\n\n1. Basic components:\n- Concealing the source of illegally obtained money\n- Transforming criminal proceeds into seemingly legitimate funds\n- Disguising the origin of criminal proceeds\n\n2. Key elements often include:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (creating complex transactions to obscure origin)\n- Integration (making funds appear legitimate)\n\n3. Specific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve:\n- Intentional financial transactions\n- Knowing the funds derive from criminal activity\n- Attempting to conceal the source of funds\n\n4. Common predicate crimes include:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Corruption\n- Organized crime\n- Terrorism financing\n\n5. Penalties typically involve:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset forfeiture\n\nFor precise legal specifics, I recommend consulting local statutes or a legal professional, as definitions can vary between countries and jurisdictions.",
